<% content_for :mermaid, true %>

<div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center mb-3">
  <h2>OSCAL Document Relationship Overview</h2>
  <%= link_to "Back to Dashboard", root_path, class: "btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" %>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <p class="text-body-secondary mb-3">
      This diagram shows how OSCAL document types connect across the three main layers
      (Control, Implementation, Assessment) and how external framework mappings integrate
      into the control ecosystem. Arrows indicate import and traceability relationships.
    </p>

    <div class="mermaid">
flowchart TB
    subgraph CL["<b>Control Layer</b>"]
        direction TB
        ExtCatalog["External Catalog<br/><small>(e.g., ISO 27001, CIS)</small>"]
        Catalog["<b>Control Catalog</b><br/><small>(e.g., NIST SP 800-53)</small>"]
        ControlMapping["<b>Control Mapping</b><br/><small>(Relationships: equivalent,<br/>subset, superset, intersects)</small>"]
        Profile["<b>Profile / Baseline</b><br/><small>(Tailored control selection<br/>+ parameter values)</small>"]
    end

    subgraph IL["<b>Implementation Layer</b>"]
        direction TB
        CDEF["<b>Component Definition</b><br/><small>(Reusable security<br/>implementations per component)</small>"]
        SSP["<b>System Security Plan</b><br/><small>(System characteristics,<br/>control implementations,<br/>components, inventory)</small>"]
    end

    subgraph AL["<b>Assessment Layer</b>"]
        direction TB
        SAP["<b>Assessment Plan</b><br/><small>(Scope, methods, schedule,<br/>assessor assignments)</small>"]
        SAR["<b>Assessment Results</b><br/><small>(Findings, observations,<br/>risks, evidence)</small>"]
        POAM["<b>Plan of Action &amp; Milestones</b><br/><small>(Remediation tracking,<br/>risk status, milestones)</small>"]
    end

    subgraph EL["<b>Enterprise</b>"]
        direction TB
        Org["<b>Organization</b>"]
        AB["<b>Authorization Boundary</b><br/><small>(ATO Package root)</small>"]
    end

    ExtCatalog -- "Mapped via<br/>Control Mapping Model" --> ControlMapping
    ControlMapping -- "Integrates into" --> Catalog
    Catalog -- "Imported &amp;<br/>tailored by" --> Profile
    Profile -- "Baseline controls<br/>imported by" --> SSP
    Profile -- "Controls feed into" --> CDEF
    Profile -- "Controls feed into" --> SAP
    CDEF -- "Component implementations<br/>auto-fill" --> SSP
    SSP -- "Assessed by" --> SAP
    SAP -- "Produces" --> SAR
    SAR -- "Unsatisfied findings<br/>generate" --> POAM
    Org -- "Contains" --> AB
    AB -- "Links to" --> SSP
    AB -- "Links to" --> SAP
    AB -- "Links to" --> SAR
    AB -- "Links to" --> POAM

    classDef control fill:#3498db,stroke:#2980b9,color:#fff
    classDef impl fill:#27ae60,stroke:#229954,color:#fff
    classDef assess fill:#e67e22,stroke:#d35400,color:#fff
    classDef enterprise fill:#9b59b6,stroke:#8e44ad,color:#fff
    classDef external fill:#95a5a6,stroke:#7f8c8d,color:#fff

    class Catalog,Profile,ControlMapping control
    class CDEF,SSP impl
    class SAP,SAR,POAM assess
    class Org,AB enterprise
    class ExtCatalog external
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%# ── Layer Descriptions ── %>
<div class="row g-3 mb-4">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card h-100" style="border-left: 4px solid #3498db;">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 style="color: #3498db;">Control Layer</h5>
        <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0">
          Defines the security controls available for selection. <strong>Catalogs</strong> contain
          the full control library (e.g., NIST SP 800-53). <strong>Profiles</strong> tailor a catalog
          into a baseline by selecting controls, setting parameters, and assigning priorities.
          <strong>Control Mappings</strong> relate controls across different frameworks
          (e.g., NIST to ISO 27001).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card h-100" style="border-left: 4px solid #27ae60;">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 style="color: #27ae60;">Implementation Layer</h5>
        <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0">
          Describes how controls are implemented. <strong>Component Definitions</strong> document
          reusable security capabilities of individual components. The <strong>System Security Plan</strong>
          combines the baseline, components, system characteristics, and per-control implementation
          statements into the authoritative system description.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <div class="card h-100" style="border-left: 4px solid #e67e22;">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h5 style="color: #e67e22;">Assessment Layer</h5>
        <p class="text-body-secondary small mb-0">
          Evaluates whether controls are correctly implemented. The <strong>Assessment Plan</strong>
          defines scope, methods, and schedule. <strong>Assessment Results</strong> capture findings,
          observations, and risks. The <strong>POA&amp;M</strong> tracks remediation of
          unsatisfied findings through milestones and status updates.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

